🛒 Best Buy Retail Store: POS Quick-Start Guide
System Version: 1.0
Status: Operational
1. Starting a Transaction
 * When the system is active, select Option 1 (New Transaction).
 * The Product Catalog will appear. Note the Item Name and Price.
 * Low Stock Alert: If you see (LOW!) next to an item, inform the manager that we have fewer than 5 units left.
2. Managing the Cart
 * To Add Items: Select 1. Type the item name (e.g., Milk) and the quantity. The system will automatically check if we have enough in stock.
 * To View Progress: Select 2 at any time to see what’s currently in the customer's basket.
 * To Fix a Mistake: Select 3 to remove a specific item. The system will automatically put that item back into our inventory count.
3. Discounts & Taxes
 * Automatic Tax: A 10% sales tax is added to every order automatically.
 * Bulk Discount: If a customer spends more than $5,000.00, the system automatically applies a 5% discount to their subtotal before tax. You don't need to do any manual math!
4. Checkout & Payment
 * Select 4 to finalize the sale.
 * The System Calculates:
   * Subtotal
   * Discount (if applicable)
   * Tax
   * Total Due
 * Input Payment: Enter the exact amount the customer gives you.
   * Note: If the amount is less than the Total Due, the system will tell you the remaining balance.
 * Change: The system calculates the exact change to return to the customer.
5. Troubleshooting & Safety
 * Cancellations: If a customer walks away, select Option 5 (Cancel). This clears the cart and restores all items to the store's stock levels.
 * Invalid Inputs: If you accidentally type a letter instead of a number for the quantity, don't worry—the system will simply ask you to try again without crashing.
💡 Pro-Tip for Cashiers:
Always type the item name exactly as it appears in the menu (e.g., use "Detergent" instead of "Soap Powder"). The system is case-sensitive but I've programmed it to handle basic capitalization!
